## PREAMBLE

The Authentic Open License, Version 1.0 ("License"), is a file-level weak copyleft license designed to promote the free use, modification, and distribution of software while ensuring that improvements to individually Licensed Files are returned to the commons. This License expressly rejects project-wide license propagation and disclaims any encumbrance upon independent works that interact with Licensed Files solely through their published application programming interfaces or documented data exchange protocols.

This License is grounded in the following convictions:

**(a)** Copyright subsists in the expressive output of individual authors, not in the combinatory act of software integration. No license may, by its own terms, impose obligations upon works in which the copyright holder has not consented to such an encumbrance.

**(b)** A copyleft obligation proportionate in scope -- attaching to derivative works of Licensed Files but not to software that merely interfaces with those files -- best achieves the balance between openness and practical usability.

**(c)** Quantitative metrics are an imprecise and gameable proxy for the qualitative legal question of whether a work is derivative. This License therefore employs a functional standard to distinguish modifications that give rise to a derivative work from those that do not.

**(d)** The legal autonomy of each copyright holder is inviolable. No license operative upon one component of a Combined Work may, without the consent of the relevant copyright holders, alter the licensing terms of any other component.

To protect these principles, this License imposes the following principal commitments: modifications to Licensed Files must themselves be released under this License upon Public Conveyance; software that merely interacts with Licensed Files through their documented interfaces is not encumbered; and no party may impose conditions on downstream recipients beyond those set forth herein.

---

## SECTION 0 -- DEFINITIONS

As used in this License, the following terms shall have the meanings set forth below.

**0.1 "License"** means this Authentic Open License, Version 1.0.

**0.2 "Licensor"** means the copyright holder or holders of a Licensed File, or any entity duly authorized by those copyright holders to grant rights under this License.

**0.3 "Licensee"** or **"You"** means any individual or legal entity exercising rights granted under this License.

**0.4 "Source Form"** means the preferred form of a work for making modifications, including but not limited to software source code, documentation source, build configuration files, and interface definition files.

**0.5 "Object Form"** means any form resulting from the mechanical transformation or translation of a Source Form, including but not limited to compiled object code, generated documentation, and media conversions.

**0.6 "Licensed File"** means any individual file, whether in Source Form or Object Form, that bears a notice placed by the Licensor indicating that it is subject to the terms of this License, or that is expressly identified as a Licensed File in project documentation maintained by the Licensor.

**0.7 "Derivative Work"** means any work, whether in Source Form or Object Form, that is based upon, adapted from, or incorporates a Licensed File in a manner that requires copyright permission -- namely, any work in which the protectable expression of the Licensed File is reproduced, adapted, or transformed.

For the avoidance of doubt:

> **(a)** A work constitutes a Derivative Work of a Licensed File only if it incorporates, adapts, or transforms the substantive expressive content of that Licensed File -- including its algorithms, data structures, control flow logic, or functional architecture -- such that a court of competent jurisdiction would recognize a copyright relationship between the original and the resulting work.

> **(b)** A work does **not** constitute a Derivative Work of a Licensed File solely by reason of:
> - (i) compilation against, linking with, or dynamic loading of the Licensed File or its Object Form;
> - (ii) invocation of Licensed File functionality at runtime through its Application Programming Interface;
> - (iii) implementation of, or compliance with, an interface declaration or data type definition published by the Licensed File, where such declarations do not themselves constitute original protectable expression;
> - (iv) use of data formats, network protocols, or interchange schemas defined or employed by the Licensed File; or
> - (v) shared occupancy of a runtime environment, process space, or operating system context with the Licensed File.

**0.8 "Covered Derivative Work"** means a Derivative Work of a Licensed File that is Conveyed by or on behalf of the Licensee.

**0.9 "Independent Module"** means a software component, library, application, service, or other work that:

> **(a)** is not a Derivative Work of any Licensed File;
> **(b)** communicates with Licensed Files exclusively through their published Application Programming Interfaces or documented data exchange protocols; and
> **(c)** is maintained or developed independently of the Licensed Files.

An Independent Module is **not** encumbered by the copyleft provisions of this License, regardless of whether it is compiled, linked, packaged, or distributed together with Licensed Files.

**0.10 "Application Programming Interface"** or **"API"** means the set of declarations, function signatures, data type definitions, interface specifications, and documented behavioral contracts through which a Licensed File exposes its functionality to external callers -- without requiring those callers to incorporate or reproduce the internal implementation of the Licensed File.

**0.11 "Combined Work"** means a work that is assembled from, or otherwise incorporates, one or more Licensed Files together with one or more Independent Modules, irrespective of whether such components are statically linked, dynamically linked, packaged together, or distributed as a collection.

**0.12 "Propagate"** means any reproduction, copying, or internal transmission of a work, whether within a single organization or between systems under common control, that does not constitute Conveyance.

**0.13 "Convey"** or **"Conveyance"** means any act by which a copy of a work is transferred to, or made available for use or download by, a third party, whether for consideration or without, including but not limited to:

> - (a) publication to a publicly accessible repository, registry, or website;
> - (b) distribution in physical or electronic media;
> - (c) making available over a network for downloading, streaming, or remote execution; and
> - (d) commercial licensing, sublicensing, or transfer.

Conveyance does **not** include internal Propagation within a single legal entity, or the transfer of copies solely for the Licensee's personal use on systems the Licensee controls.

**0.14 "Public Conveyance"** means any Conveyance that makes the work available to any recipient without a pre-existing confidentiality obligation, or to recipients not individually identified and authorized by the Licensor prior to Conveyance.

**0.15 "Private Conveyance"** means Conveyance of copies solely to specifically identified recipients under conditions that restrict further redistribution, solely for non-commercial purposes, through private or access-controlled channels.

**0.16 "Corresponding Source"** means all Source Form necessary to compile, build, reproduce, and install the Object Form of a Licensed File or Covered Derivative Work, including all source files of the Licensed File or Covered Derivative Work, and all build scripts, makefiles, and configuration files required to produce the Object Form. Corresponding Source does not encompass the source code of Independent Modules, general-purpose system libraries, or development tools, except to the extent such materials are distributed together with the Object Form.

**0.17 "Material Modification"** means a modification to a Licensed File that materially alters its functional behavior, algorithmic logic, data structures, control flow, error handling, or functional architecture, and in which the modification itself constitutes original protectable expression. The following are **not** Material Modifications, regardless of their frequency or aggregate volume:

> - (a) changes to formatting, indentation, or whitespace;
> - (b) additions, removals, or alterations to comments or documentation strings;
> - (c) renaming of identifiers, functions, variables, classes, or files without altering their behavior;
> - (d) syntactic refactoring that preserves observable behavior; and
> - (e) isolated defect corrections that restore intended behavior without altering architecture.

**0.18 "Attribution Information"** means all copyright notices, authorship attributions, license headers, and any additional notices required under Section 4.2 that are contained in or associated with a Licensed File.

