## SECTION 3 -- PERSONAL USE AND PRIVATE CONVEYANCE

**3.1 Personal Use.** You may reproduce and Propagate Licensed Files, with or without modification, solely for Your own personal or internal organizational use, without attribution, license notice, or any other compliance obligation under this License.

**3.2 Private Conveyance.** You may Convey Licensed Files or Covered Derivative Works by means of Private Conveyance -- including to specifically identified recipients through access-controlled, non-commercial channels -- without attribution, license notice, or source availability requirements.

The Licensor expressly waives the right to pursue legal action against any party engaged in good-faith private or small-scale non-commercial sharing of Licensed Files. This License imposes no compliance obligations upon Private Conveyance.

---

## SECTION 4 -- COPYLEFT OBLIGATION FOR PUBLIC CONVEYANCE

**4.1 Scope of Copyleft.** If You Publicly Convey a Covered Derivative Work, You must:

> **(a)** license the Covered Derivative Work under this License, with all terms intact and unmodified;
> **(b)** preserve all Attribution Information in each Licensed File included in or forming the basis of the Covered Derivative Work;
> **(c)** make the Corresponding Source available in accordance with Section 6; and
> **(d)** include, in a location reasonably prominent to recipients, a notice identifying the original Licensed File(s) upon which the Covered Derivative Work is based.

**4.2 Notice of Modification.** If You make Material Modifications to a Licensed File and Publicly Convey the result, You must add a notice within the modified file identifying:

> **(a)** the nature of the modification;
> **(b)** the identity of the modifying party; and
> **(c)** the date on which the modification was made.

Such notice must not represent that the original Licensor endorsed or is responsible for the modified work.

**4.3 No Additional Encumbrances.** You may not impose any legal terms, technological protection measures, or contractual restrictions upon recipients of Covered Derivative Works that restrict or purport to restrict the exercise of rights granted to those recipients by this License.

---

## SECTION 5 -- INTERFACE EXCEPTION: INDEPENDENT MODULES NOT ENCUMBERED

**5.1 Disclaimer of Viral Effect.** The copyleft provisions of Section 4 do not extend to Independent Modules. No obligation under this License attaches to any Independent Module solely because it:

> **(a)** is compiled, linked, or assembled together with one or more Licensed Files into a Combined Work;
> **(b)** calls functions, methods, or procedures exported by a Licensed File through its Application Programming Interface;
> **(c)** implements, references, or derives from interface declarations, schemas, or data type definitions published by a Licensed File, where those declarations do not themselves constitute original copyrightable expression proprietary to the Licensor;
> **(d)** shares a runtime environment, address space, or operating system context with a Licensed File; or
> **(e)** is packaged or distributed in the same repository, archive, or release artifact as a Licensed File.

**5.2 Conveyance of Combined Works.** You may create and Publicly Convey a Combined Work incorporating Licensed Files together with Independent Modules, provided that:

> **(a)** Licensed Files within the Combined Work are conveyed in compliance with this License;
> **(b)** Independent Modules within the Combined Work are conveyed under their own respective licenses, free of any restriction imposed by this License; and
> **(c)** the terms governing Independent Modules do not restrict recipients from replacing or modifying the Licensed Files within the Combined Work.

**5.3 Construction of Interface Exception.** The interface exception set forth in this Section shall be construed broadly and in favor of the Licensee. The Licensor expressly disavows any interpretation of this License that would encumber Independent Modules with its copyleft obligations by reason only of their interaction with, inclusion alongside, or runtime co-existence with Licensed Files.

