## SECTION 6 -- CONVEYANCE IN SOURCE AND OBJECT FORM

**6.1 Conveyance in Source Form.** You may Publicly Convey a Licensed File or Covered Derivative Work in Source Form, provided You comply with Section 4.

**6.2 Conveyance in Object Form.** You may Publicly Convey a Licensed File or Covered Derivative Work in Object Form, provided that You also fulfill **one** of the following:

> **(a)** accompany the Object Form with a complete, machine-readable copy of the Corresponding Source, delivered on a physical or electronic medium commonly used for software exchange;
> **(b)** provide, alongside the Object Form, a written offer -- valid for a period of not less than three (3) years from the date of Conveyance -- to furnish the Corresponding Source to any requesting party upon request and without additional charge; or
> **(c)** make the Corresponding Source continuously available from a publicly accessible network location at no charge, for so long as Object Form remains available from that location.

**6.3 Anti-Lockdown Provision.** If You Convey a Licensed File or Covered Derivative Work in Object Form as part of a device or embedded system in which the installation of modified versions of the Object Form is restricted or prevented by technological or contractual means, You must provide the recipient with all information, cryptographic keys, and authorizations within Your legal control that are necessary to install modified versions on the device. This obligation does not require You to provide warranty, support, or indemnification for any modified installation.

