## SECTION 7 -- RELICENSING OF MATERIALLY MODIFIED COVERED DERIVATIVE WORKS

**7.1 General Rule.** Licensed Files must remain under this License upon Public Conveyance, except as expressly provided in this Section.

**7.2 Permission to Relicense.** You may relicense a Covered Derivative Work -- thereby releasing it under a license other than this License -- if and only if all of the following conditions are satisfied:

> **(a) Material Modification.** The Covered Derivative Work incorporates Material Modifications, as defined in Section 0.17, that constitute a substantial and independent creative or technical contribution, and not merely cosmetic, incidental, or trivially additive alterations.

> **(b) Copyright Ownership and Consent.** You hold copyright in the Material Modifications. The question of whether contributor consent is required for relicensing is determined by a single test: whether protectable expression from the original Licensed File -- specifically, its algorithms, data structures, control flow logic, or functional architecture as originally expressed -- has been reproduced or adapted into the Covered Derivative Work in a form that would be actionable as copyright infringement absent a license.
>
> Where no such expression survives into the Covered Derivative Work, relicensing proceeds without contributor consent.
>
> Where such expression survives, You must obtain written consent from the copyright holders of the surviving portions only. Consent is not required from contributors whose expression does not survive into the Covered Derivative Work.
>
> For clarity: the complete rewrite of a Licensed File in a different programming language, or the complete replacement of its algorithms with independently developed alternatives, extinguishes the original expression and requires no contributor consent.

> **(c) Attribution Preserved.** Each file in the relicensed Covered Derivative Work that incorporates material from a Licensed File must bear the following notice:

```
/*
 * This file contains material originally from [Original Project],
 * authored by [Original Author(s)], and licensed under the
 * Authentic Open License, Version 1.0.
 * Substantially modified by [Your Name or Organization].
 * This file is now distributed under: [New License Name and URL].
 */
```

**7.3 New Files.** Files that You create independently, and that are not Derivative Works of any Licensed File, are not encumbered by this License and may be licensed under any terms You choose.

**7.4 Failure to Qualify.** Where the conditions of Section 7.2 are not satisfied, the Covered Derivative Work must remain under this License and all provisions hereof apply without exception.

