## SECTION 9 -- TERMINATION

**9.1 Automatic Termination.** Your rights to Publicly Convey Licensed Files or Covered Derivative Works terminate automatically, without requirement of notice, upon any material breach of the obligations set forth in Sections 4, 5.2, or 6. Such termination:

> **(a)** does not affect Your right to Propagate Licensed Files for personal use;
> **(b)** does not affect Your right of Private Conveyance;
> **(c)** does not affect the rights of any third party who received Licensed Files from You in full compliance with this License prior to termination; and
> **(d)** does not affect the rights of other Licensees.

**9.2 Reinstatement.** Terminated rights are automatically reinstated if You cure the material breach within thirty (30) days of receiving written notice thereof from the Licensor, and provide written confirmation of compliance to the Licensor. Where a breach is cured and confirmed within the thirty-day period, no legal action based solely upon that breach may thereafter be commenced by the Licensor.

**9.3 Non-Waiver.** The Licensor's failure to enforce any provision of this License in any particular instance shall not constitute a waiver of the right to enforce that provision in any other instance.

